1
00:00:21,930 --> 00:00:24,480
Than, what are you doing?
Why not turn on the lights?

2
00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:28,140
Why light candles like this?

3
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:29,920
You could set the room on fire.

4
00:00:44,830 --> 00:00:46,600
Is there a campfire show at school?

5
00:00:46,690 --> 00:00:47,690
What are you wearing?

6
00:00:48,760 --> 00:00:52,050
Kin, someone once told me

7
00:00:52,890 --> 00:00:54,440
if you love someone, say it fast

8
00:00:55,290 --> 00:00:57,290
I’m scared someone might
steal you from me.

9
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:02,060
I may just be a high school kid to you

10
00:01:03,080 --> 00:01:04,569
but this high school kid

11
00:01:07,020 --> 00:01:08,070
really loves you, Kin.

12
00:01:16,950 --> 00:01:18,130
Let me get engaged to you first.

13
00:01:19,210 --> 00:01:22,150
When I grow up and get a job,

14
00:01:23,190 --> 00:01:25,110
I’ll buy a real ring
to replace this one.

15
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,950
What are you playing at, Than?

16
00:01:32,340 --> 00:01:35,300
You might see me as a kid
who knows nothing about love

17
00:01:35,970 --> 00:01:37,509
but look into my eyes,

18
00:01:38,860 --> 00:01:39,710
what do you see?

19
00:01:45,820 --> 00:01:46,350
I see it.

20
00:01:47,490 --> 00:01:48,479
Eye gunk.

21
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:51,410
Be serious.

22
00:01:52,210 --> 00:01:54,539
I am serious. Come on.

23
00:01:55,380 --> 00:01:58,020
So how would being engaged
be different?

24
00:01:59,330 --> 00:02:01,250
It would make you feel secure.

25
00:02:01,990 --> 00:02:03,770
Like a promise between us

26
00:02:03,970 --> 00:02:06,440
that we’re not just boyfriends

27
00:02:06,750 --> 00:02:07,700
but something more.

28
00:02:08,430 --> 00:02:10,310
I don’t really know
how it’s supposed to be.

29
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:13,940
I’ve never had a boyfriend,
this is my first love

30
00:02:14,490 --> 00:02:15,990
I just want to do my best

31
00:02:16,660 --> 00:02:19,670
to be better every day we’re together.

32
00:02:21,060 --> 00:02:22,079
Thank you.

33
00:02:44,270 --> 00:02:46,620
I don’t know what
the future will be like

34
00:02:48,180 --> 00:02:50,950
but I’ll love you more
every single day

35
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,550
and love you the best I can.

36
00:02:54,610 --> 00:02:56,410
I’ll love you the best I can too.

37
00:03:05,890 --> 00:03:07,060
Than, that’s enough.

38
00:03:13,170 --> 00:03:13,950
What’s that smell, Than?

39
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:17,800
Does something smell burnt?

40
00:03:29,690 --> 00:03:32,310
This is how hot my love for you is.

41
00:04:36,190 --> 00:04:37,900
I’m so happy.

42
00:04:39,210 --> 00:04:40,970
It was worth the long wait.

43
00:04:41,810 --> 00:04:43,100
I promise you, Than

44
00:04:43,750 --> 00:04:46,400
that I’ll never walk out
of your life again.

45
00:04:46,790 --> 00:04:48,350
Don’t think we didn’t see you.

46
00:04:48,420 --> 00:04:50,320
Take those two in for questioning.

47
00:04:50,460 --> 00:04:52,610
- Let's go.
- Let’s go, Than.

48
00:04:52,970 --> 00:04:54,430
Someone wants to see you.

49
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:57,240
Meya, Mawin’s mother.

50
00:04:57,830 --> 00:04:58,770
Hello.

51
00:04:59,860 --> 00:05:01,670
If something makes you wait,

52
00:05:02,340 --> 00:05:03,780
can you wait for me again?

53
00:05:12,590 --> 00:05:13,430
When do you have to go?

54
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:16,740
My mom wants me to go
as soon as possible

55
00:05:18,140 --> 00:05:20,140
but the doctors there
haven’t said anything for sure.

56
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:24,960
What about your work here?

57
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,320
I’ll have to talk to Too first.

58
00:05:33,060 --> 00:05:34,510
You’ll wait for me, right?

59
00:05:39,490 --> 00:05:42,820
Last time, you left
without saying a word.

60
00:05:43,460 --> 00:05:45,250
I didn’t even know
when you’d come back

61
00:05:45,620 --> 00:05:46,750
and I still waited.

62
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:52,590
This time, I know you’re going

63
00:05:54,260 --> 00:05:56,200
and I know how to reach you.

64
00:05:57,420 --> 00:06:00,370
And in the end, you’ll come back.

65
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:14,730
We both have families.

66
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,340
Parents we need to care for.

67
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,540
Choosing our families

68
00:06:21,990 --> 00:06:24,690
doesn’t mean we love each other
any less, Kin.

69
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:28,950
It means understanding

70
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:33,260
that love is bigger
than just the two of us, Kin.

71
00:06:41,540 --> 00:06:42,960
Go do what you have to do.

72
00:06:43,890 --> 00:06:47,800
One day, it will beour time.

73
00:06:49,670 --> 00:06:50,510
Thank you, Than.

74
00:07:31,940 --> 00:07:32,980
Daddy Kin.

75
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:35,659
When you get there, please call us.

76
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:36,550
I will.

77
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,860
Yes, please call us often too.

78
00:07:43,830 --> 00:07:45,830
Don’t worry about things here, Kin.

79
00:07:46,159 --> 00:07:47,670
Yes, don’t worry at all.

80
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:51,290
We’ll take care of Uncle Than for you.

81
00:07:51,730 --> 00:07:55,380
Yes, leave it to the two of us.

82
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:56,680
Okay.

83
00:07:59,450 --> 00:08:00,770
Don’t worry, Kin.

84
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:04,140
Because every minute I wait for you

85
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:08,060
is proof of how much you mean to me.

86
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:13,490
Our love hasn’t stopped,

87
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:17,960
it keeps moving forward
with hope we’ll be together.

88
00:08:19,150 --> 00:08:23,420
Let’s start again
with the same hearts.

89
00:08:24,660 --> 00:08:25,500
Me too.

90
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:27,190
Me too.

91
00:10:04,550 --> 00:10:05,920
In our lives,

92
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,580
we may come across good moments

93
00:10:08,770 --> 00:10:10,100
and bad ones,

94
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:13,930
or sometimes terrible ones,

95
00:10:14,570 --> 00:10:16,820
mixed through
different stages of life.

96
00:10:18,550 --> 00:10:22,030
Sometimes, no matter how hard we try,

97
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:26,190
it doesn’t mean success
will always wait for us.

98
00:10:28,610 --> 00:10:33,260
Life will have disappointments,
things won’t go as planned.

99
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:38,940
Just because we survived a major storm
doesn’t mean we won’t fall again

100
00:10:39,450 --> 00:10:43,110
but we learn how to rise with pride.

101
00:10:46,180 --> 00:10:48,940
Here, Nene and Mawin made it for me.

102
00:10:48,940 --> 00:10:49,940
Cute?

103
00:10:50,990 --> 00:10:55,270
Relationships today
aren’t afraid of distance.

104
00:10:55,990 --> 00:10:58,130
- Even across continents,
- Yes.

105
00:10:58,340 --> 00:11:01,090
we can still look into each other’s
eyes through the screen every night.

106
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:03,540
I see it. I love it. Thank you, Than

107
00:11:05,090 --> 00:11:06,860
I made it myself too.

108
00:11:08,090 --> 00:11:09,620
I helped too.

109
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:11,310
I helped as well.

110
00:11:11,730 --> 00:11:15,100
- I helped too.
- We all helped.

111
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:17,880
How is it over there?
Are you okay?

112
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:22,280
Sometimes waiting helps us understand

113
00:11:22,710 --> 00:11:25,160
true love is never in a rush.

114
00:11:30,590 --> 00:11:32,570
I believe time changes our lives

115
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:34,530
and life changes us

116
00:11:35,060 --> 00:11:37,120
whether we’re ready or not.

117
00:11:37,150 --> 00:11:39,690
Here’s the menu,
and the drink menu as well

118
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:44,970
We also recommend the cold cuts.

119
00:11:44,990 --> 00:11:46,990
Cold cuts then,
one order of cold cuts.

120
00:11:56,100 --> 00:11:57,070
Do you remember this song?

121
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:00,850
Shall we dance?

122
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,300
Excuse me for a moment.

123
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:04,220
Such a big smile. Look.

124
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:05,750
Happiness

125
00:12:05,930 --> 00:12:10,190
sometimes doesn’t come
from chasing things.

126
00:12:11,460 --> 00:12:12,380
This is a soft song.

127
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:15,980
But from accepting what comes our way

128
00:12:19,270 --> 00:12:22,040
and understanding every story in life.

129
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:36,440
Change may be scary today,

130
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:39,720
but one day we’ll thank it.

131
00:12:48,370 --> 00:12:52,670
Once, something happened
that pulled Kin and me apart

132
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:57,290
but I was lucky we found our way back.

133
00:13:04,630 --> 00:13:07,940
It let me fix what was left unresolved

134
00:13:08,610 --> 00:13:10,970
and helped us love each other again.

135
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:15,320
Maybe even more than before

136
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:21,120
because we’ve tasted
what separation feels like.

137
00:13:29,470 --> 00:13:30,660
Hello, Kin.

138
00:13:32,010 --> 00:13:33,080
Than, what are you doing?

139
00:13:34,060 --> 00:13:35,780
I’m at my parents’ place.

140
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:38,080
Nene and Mawin are here too.

141
00:13:42,310 --> 00:13:44,520
Kids, say hi to Uncle Kin.

142
00:13:44,550 --> 00:13:46,040
- Hello.
- Hello.

143
00:13:47,290 --> 00:13:48,360
What are you doing?

144
00:13:48,650 --> 00:13:50,130
Playing with toys.

145
00:13:50,650 --> 00:13:53,050
Hello, Mawin. Hello, Nene.

146
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:54,840
Bye-bye.

147
00:13:54,870 --> 00:13:57,820
Because we’ve tasted
what separation feels like,

148
00:13:59,050 --> 00:14:00,880
the lesson of distance

149
00:14:01,450 --> 00:14:06,430
teaches us to hold on
to each other as long as we can.

150
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:07,020
Bye-bye.

151
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:12,770
But if Kin and I hadn’t taken
the long road of goodbye

152
00:14:13,070 --> 00:14:14,320
on the road of love

153
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:18,210
just to find each other again,

154
00:14:18,870 --> 00:14:20,440
what would our story be like?

155
00:14:34,140 --> 00:14:35,540
Play carefully, you’ll fall again.

156
00:14:47,390 --> 00:14:49,680
- Hello.
- It’s Meya.

157
00:14:50,090 --> 00:14:53,430
- Well...
- I’m calling to say I’m pregnant.

158
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,910
I met him three months ago.

159
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,670
He was a camera assistant.

160
00:15:02,420 --> 00:15:04,140
But I didn’t know his name.

161
00:15:05,390 --> 00:15:06,340
A camera assistant?

162
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:11,770
Is it this guy?

163
00:15:18,340 --> 00:15:19,430
Yes, that’s him.

164
00:15:20,030 --> 00:15:22,500
That’s Sun. He’s my older brother.

165
00:15:23,420 --> 00:15:24,270
Oh.

166
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:54,440
Hey, are you tired today?

167
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:55,910
I’m fine.

168
00:15:56,460 --> 00:15:57,390
Let’s go. We should head back.

169
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:58,810
Than, you drive.

170
00:16:02,640 --> 00:16:06,820
Today, Thailand reported
96 new COVID-19 cases.

171
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:10,480
Total confirmed cases are now 24,890.

172
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:12,830
106 patients have recovered.

173
00:16:51,660 --> 00:16:53,000
Even if we’re apart for a while,

174
00:16:53,560 --> 00:16:55,810
our hearts aren’t in quarantine.

175
00:17:12,609 --> 00:17:14,329
Happy Valentine’s Day.

176
00:17:14,740 --> 00:17:17,930
And congrats on becoming
the new Creative Director.

177
00:17:23,750 --> 00:17:24,300
Thanks.

178
00:17:24,740 --> 00:17:26,660
- Same as always, right?
- Thank you.

179
00:17:27,190 --> 00:17:28,000
Thank you so much.

180
00:17:37,830 --> 00:17:38,310
Smells so good.

181
00:17:39,490 --> 00:17:40,360
Than.

182
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:43,270
Bunny.

183
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:55,710
Than, smile. One, two, three.

184
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:58,170
Great. Mom and Dad, please come in.

185
00:17:59,040 --> 00:18:01,510
Let’s count. One, two, three.

186
00:18:14,350 --> 00:18:15,450
Congratulations.

187
00:18:15,940 --> 00:18:17,780
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

188
00:18:17,890 --> 00:18:21,130
Alright, one more shot.
One, two, three.

189
00:18:22,940 --> 00:18:23,580
Heading back already?

190
00:18:24,170 --> 00:18:26,070
Yes. Than’s closing the gym today.

191
00:18:27,170 --> 00:18:29,080
Good timing, Kin.
You can help him close.

192
00:18:29,890 --> 00:18:30,970
I’ll leave it to you. I’m heading out.

193
00:18:31,220 --> 00:18:31,620
Okay.

194
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:48,820
I really miss you, Kin.

195
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:50,000
Give me a kiss.

196
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:52,520
A kiss? I’ve been working all day.

197
00:18:53,860 --> 00:18:58,200
No, I mean you kiss me.

198
00:18:59,280 --> 00:18:59,730
Right here.

199
00:19:02,010 --> 00:19:02,570
And here too.

200
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:04,420
Here.

201
00:19:07,330 --> 00:19:08,040
Again.

202
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:14,700
That’s enough. Someone might see.

203
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:18,020
Who would? The gym is closed.

204
00:19:39,050 --> 00:19:40,440
Oh, here it is.

205
00:19:41,460 --> 00:19:44,860
Hey, Than, you’re still not home?

206
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:47,590
Help take down the standee too.

207
00:19:48,290 --> 00:19:51,820
Sure. Please help turn off
the counter lights.

208
00:19:52,570 --> 00:19:53,240
Okay.

209
00:19:55,380 --> 00:19:56,160
I’ll head out then.

210
00:19:57,430 --> 00:19:58,030
Got it.

211
00:20:03,990 --> 00:20:06,540
Now no one will see us for sure.

212
00:20:09,230 --> 00:20:09,910
You should go now.

213
00:20:12,290 --> 00:20:16,680
I don’t know why I missed you all day.

214
00:20:17,580 --> 00:20:20,980
I can’t wait
until we get back to the condo.

215
00:20:30,350 --> 00:20:31,910
You smell so good, Kin.

216
00:20:32,950 --> 00:20:35,410
Your cologne really lingers,
doesn’t it?

217
00:20:36,390 --> 00:20:37,240
Enough.

218
00:20:38,420 --> 00:20:40,620
Your boyfriend owns the gym,

219
00:20:41,280 --> 00:20:44,280
we should get
some off-schedule training.

220
00:20:55,500 --> 00:20:57,280
That’s enough, Than.

221
00:20:58,130 --> 00:20:59,170
Not enough.

222
00:21:14,950 --> 00:21:17,340
Then, the usual place?

223
00:21:19,070 --> 00:21:19,750
The locker room.

224
00:23:00,920 --> 00:23:02,690
In real life,

225
00:23:02,830 --> 00:23:05,700
no matter what our love story
turns out to be,

226
00:23:06,430 --> 00:23:10,150
in the end, our paths
have led us back together.

227
00:23:10,840 --> 00:23:12,670
We found each other again.

228
00:23:12,990 --> 00:23:15,740
Many couples never even get
a chance to say goodbye,

229
00:23:16,030 --> 00:23:20,910
but I’m lucky to say
“I love you” once more.

230
00:23:27,420 --> 00:23:29,520
Can you do it? Is it hard?

231
00:23:30,330 --> 00:23:31,550
Is it hard?

232
00:23:32,260 --> 00:23:32,830
Everyone,

233
00:23:33,910 --> 00:23:36,080
look who I brought today.

234
00:23:38,380 --> 00:23:39,230
Kin.

235
00:23:40,060 --> 00:23:41,120
Hello, Mom and Dad.

236
00:23:41,470 --> 00:23:42,670
- Hello, dear.
- Hello, dear.

237
00:23:44,100 --> 00:23:45,040
Uncle Kin.

238
00:23:50,500 --> 00:23:53,260
Look at that.

239
00:23:54,960 --> 00:23:58,490
- Look at Nene. Look at her smile.
- So happy.

240
00:24:00,080 --> 00:24:02,080
Some people fear starting over,

241
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:08,320
but for me, starting again
with this same heart

242
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:10,240
is totally worth it.

243
00:24:14,540 --> 00:24:16,770
Oh, oh, here they come.

244
00:24:28,150 --> 00:24:29,750
Thank you.

245
00:25:38,010 --> 00:25:39,080
Thank you, Nene.

246
00:26:20,890 --> 00:26:21,380
Thank you.

247
00:26:58,840 --> 00:27:01,890
So proud of you. You did great.

248
00:27:17,130 --> 00:27:19,450
First of all,
I’d like to thank our guests

249
00:27:19,620 --> 00:27:23,070
for being here today
to witness our grooms.

250
00:27:24,070 --> 00:27:27,580
It feels like yesterday
when I saw little Than

251
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:31,180
playing basketball in our driveway.

252
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:35,060
- About seven years old then?
- Yes.

253
00:27:35,510 --> 00:27:38,770
I asked you why you loved basketball.

254
00:27:39,330 --> 00:27:40,560
And you told me,

255
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:45,060
“Basketball needs
both body and heart.”

256
00:27:45,630 --> 00:27:47,480
Back then, I thought

257
00:27:47,480 --> 00:27:50,610
he must have seen a TV commercial.

258
00:27:51,190 --> 00:27:54,540
But believe me, everyone,
Than proved to me

259
00:27:54,650 --> 00:27:56,280
that he truly understands
what he said.

260
00:27:57,210 --> 00:27:59,960
He gives his whole body
and heart,

261
00:28:00,780 --> 00:28:04,140
just like he gives them
to the one beside him today.

262
00:28:04,810 --> 00:28:07,340
I’m confident his love
will stay strong,

263
00:28:08,050 --> 00:28:10,470
just like every time
he’s on the court.

264
00:28:13,670 --> 00:28:17,520
Today, I feel like
I’ve gained two children.

265
00:28:18,520 --> 00:28:21,820
I believe if your brother
were still here,

266
00:28:23,280 --> 00:28:25,360
he would be so proud of you,

267
00:28:26,660 --> 00:28:28,010
just like I am now.

268
00:28:29,350 --> 00:28:31,010
I remember when Than was little,

269
00:28:31,990 --> 00:28:34,870
I asked what he wanted to be.

270
00:28:36,190 --> 00:28:40,840
He never said a doctor
or a teacher,

271
00:28:42,030 --> 00:28:45,180
or anything like other kids did.

272
00:28:47,350 --> 00:28:48,740
Instead, he said

273
00:28:49,180 --> 00:28:52,940
he wanted to be someone
who makes the one beside him laugh

274
00:28:53,270 --> 00:28:54,570
every single day.

275
00:28:55,820 --> 00:28:59,370
I wondered who would be the lucky one

276
00:29:00,370 --> 00:29:03,890
to live with someone
who makes others laugh every day,

277
00:29:05,170 --> 00:29:07,010
and that person really walked in.

278
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:11,260
He came as a big brother,

279
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:14,640
a friend, a lover,

280
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:16,790
and a home for my child.

281
00:29:18,500 --> 00:29:23,520
And someone who makes my child
a little calmer.

282
00:29:24,120 --> 00:29:25,700
Come on, Mom.

283
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:28,360
I thank you, Kin,

284
00:29:29,020 --> 00:29:32,480
for loving my child just as he is.

285
00:29:34,140 --> 00:29:35,350
Hold hands tight,

286
00:29:38,210 --> 00:29:39,730
and keep laughing together,

287
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:42,810
just like you dreamed as a child.

288
00:29:47,130 --> 00:29:51,530
Welcome to our home, our family.

289
00:29:56,550 --> 00:29:57,490
Congratulations, my dear.

290
00:30:04,870 --> 00:30:05,660
Thank you.

291
00:30:07,990 --> 00:30:11,050
Love isn’t something
everyone is lucky to find.

292
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:15,550
I believe we all have
the right to hope,

293
00:30:15,820 --> 00:30:17,420
that one day will be ours too.

294
00:30:18,110 --> 00:30:19,500
I hope so as well.

295
00:30:20,430 --> 00:30:22,630
I hope the love you two share

296
00:30:23,650 --> 00:30:25,320
becomes hope for many others

297
00:30:26,630 --> 00:30:28,380
who are still waiting
for their own love.

298
00:30:30,170 --> 00:30:33,230
Today, Kin and Than’s love

299
00:30:33,850 --> 00:30:35,930
isn’t beautiful because it’s romantic,

300
00:30:36,510 --> 00:30:38,650
it’s beautiful because it’s real.

301
00:30:39,250 --> 00:30:41,580
You both have endured so much,

302
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:43,790
and passed many tests together.

303
00:30:44,550 --> 00:30:48,350
I wish your days
are filled with understanding,

304
00:30:49,020 --> 00:30:52,340
trust, and being
each other’s support forever.

305
00:30:53,240 --> 00:30:55,740
One day, I want this too.

306
00:30:56,780 --> 00:30:59,120
I’m single, everyone.
Very single right now.

307
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:01,300
Congratulations.

308
00:31:16,170 --> 00:31:17,490
I’ll be honest.

309
00:31:20,690 --> 00:31:21,910
I loved Than deeply.

310
00:31:23,780 --> 00:31:24,710
Not “loved,” actually.

311
00:31:26,120 --> 00:31:30,440
Because I still love Than
just as much now.

312
00:31:30,540 --> 00:31:31,540
It never changed.

313
00:31:34,730 --> 00:31:36,550
So much that I even wondered

314
00:31:37,990 --> 00:31:40,890
why I could love
without expecting anything back.

315
00:31:41,290 --> 00:31:43,460
But if it didn’t work out
and he chose someone else,

316
00:31:45,920 --> 00:31:46,940
I’d be next in line.

317
00:31:49,260 --> 00:31:49,910
Hey, Nut.

318
00:31:51,110 --> 00:31:52,500
Honestly, I did hope.

319
00:31:53,290 --> 00:31:58,970
But I never got anything back
beyond being called “brother.”

320
00:31:59,800 --> 00:32:01,930
My good big brother.

321
00:32:02,930 --> 00:32:05,570
But today, I finally know

322
00:32:05,910 --> 00:32:09,970
that love isn’t about getting
what you want.

323
00:32:11,090 --> 00:32:15,040
It’s about seeing
the one you love be happy.

324
00:32:23,140 --> 00:32:24,180
And now I’ve seen it.

325
00:32:26,510 --> 00:32:29,690
Than’s happiness is you, Kin.

326
00:32:31,230 --> 00:32:32,420
I don’t regret it at all

327
00:32:32,930 --> 00:32:34,760
that I wasn’t the one he loved.

328
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:39,520
Because loving him
was something beautiful.

329
00:32:40,620 --> 00:32:43,030
Something truly good
that happened in my life.

330
00:32:47,550 --> 00:32:52,750
Oh, and there’s one more thing
he may never have known.

331
00:32:58,950 --> 00:33:00,480
I was at the basketball court
that day.

332
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:03,250
Thank you.

333
00:33:10,860 --> 00:33:12,450
The day he met you, Kin.

334
00:33:13,890 --> 00:33:15,790
But he never saw me.

335
00:33:17,340 --> 00:33:18,380
Does it hurt?

336
00:33:30,970 --> 00:33:35,100
Today, I have nothing more to say
than this one word…

337
00:33:36,230 --> 00:33:36,840
Happy.

338
00:33:38,160 --> 00:33:43,000
Happy to see the person I love most

339
00:33:44,700 --> 00:33:46,430
with the one who loves him most.

340
00:33:48,450 --> 00:33:54,520
I wish you and Kin
never have to start over again.

341
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:58,410
May you both walk forward
with certainty.

342
00:34:01,170 --> 00:34:02,220
As for me,

343
00:34:05,090 --> 00:34:09,710
I’ll watch your love with happiness.

344
00:34:11,400 --> 00:34:14,239
Congratulations.
Truly, congratulations.

345
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:23,750
Congratulations.

346
00:34:40,570 --> 00:34:45,190
Many of you may not know
I was where the chaos began.

347
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:49,020
I was the reason
your love stumbled for a while.

348
00:34:49,540 --> 00:34:50,400
Excuse me.

349
00:34:51,230 --> 00:34:52,389
For many years,

350
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:55,620
it almost made you
part forever.

351
00:34:56,889 --> 00:34:58,550
Kin, Than,

352
00:34:59,400 --> 00:35:01,620
today, I’m happier than ever

353
00:35:02,050 --> 00:35:04,660
to see you both
love each other again,

354
00:35:04,860 --> 00:35:06,090
just as it should be.

355
00:35:07,470 --> 00:35:09,510
Thank you for letting me
stand here today,

356
00:35:11,120 --> 00:35:13,400
and be part of your special day.

357
00:35:14,300 --> 00:35:17,850
May this love be your last love,

358
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:20,710
a love that never needs
to return again,

359
00:35:21,240 --> 00:35:22,570
because it will never leave.

360
00:35:23,630 --> 00:35:24,520
Congratulations.

361
00:35:24,730 --> 00:35:25,750
Thank you, Meya.

362
00:35:26,100 --> 00:35:27,040
Thank you.

363
00:35:42,790 --> 00:35:44,460
Uh, I’m not great
at speaking to crowds.

364
00:35:45,740 --> 00:35:46,880
I’m usually behind the lens.

365
00:35:47,600 --> 00:35:51,400
Today, I’m glad to see
two people deeply in love together.

366
00:35:52,280 --> 00:35:53,960
Getting the chance to love fully.

367
00:35:54,990 --> 00:35:56,970
To care for each other
while you still can.

368
00:35:57,600 --> 00:35:59,690
To say what you feel.

369
00:36:00,260 --> 00:36:02,350
To turn ordinary days
into something special.

370
00:36:05,890 --> 00:36:10,890
Someone once taught me
that sincerity truly matters.

371
00:36:12,850 --> 00:36:15,640
It’s a precious gift
we can give to those we love.

372
00:36:17,940 --> 00:36:21,500
Courage is what we need
on our weakest days.

373
00:36:22,630 --> 00:36:24,280
If you get the chance to love someone,

374
00:36:24,790 --> 00:36:26,170
love them with all your heart.

375
00:36:26,680 --> 00:36:28,310
Make every moment together count.

376
00:36:29,140 --> 00:36:33,850
Because we never know
how long we’ll have to love them.

377
00:36:35,190 --> 00:36:37,770
I’m someone who lost
that chance and that time.

378
00:36:41,290 --> 00:36:44,540
No matter what you face,
don’t let go too easily.

379
00:36:50,140 --> 00:36:51,950
Don’t wait until it’s too late
to say “I love you.”

380
00:36:55,440 --> 00:36:59,630
Because the most beautiful world
is one with the people we love,

381
00:37:03,730 --> 00:37:05,090
even if they live only in our hearts.

382
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:16,620
♪ เสียไป มันช่างมีความหมาย ♪

383
00:37:18,600 --> 00:37:22,740
♪ แค่เสียดายที่เราไม่ได้บอกลา ♪

384
00:37:32,940 --> 00:37:35,800
I wasn’t planning to say anything,

385
00:37:36,330 --> 00:37:38,570
but I want to use this moment
to tell you both,

386
00:37:39,720 --> 00:37:41,260
you two are incredible.

387
00:37:42,300 --> 00:37:43,530
You’re my idols.

388
00:37:44,500 --> 00:37:46,740
You showed me that
if you truly love someone,

389
00:37:47,620 --> 00:37:50,360
no matter the mistakes
or misunderstandings,

390
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:53,420
no matter how far it pulls you apart,

391
00:37:53,810 --> 00:37:56,760
you’ll find your way back
if the love is strong enough.

392
00:37:57,360 --> 00:37:59,150
I want a love like yours someday.

393
00:38:00,660 --> 00:38:01,750
I’m still single, everyone.

394
00:38:05,620 --> 00:38:09,230
We were once two kids
who didn’t even know how love works.

395
00:38:09,780 --> 00:38:12,610
We loved each other
without knowing how to hold on.

396
00:38:12,870 --> 00:38:14,170
And as we grew up,

397
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:16,490
we learned love isn’t just a feeling.

398
00:38:17,040 --> 00:38:18,880
We lived through days
we understood each other,

399
00:38:19,330 --> 00:38:21,220
and days we understood nothing at all

400
00:38:21,830 --> 00:38:23,690
We shared days full of smiles,

401
00:38:24,210 --> 00:38:26,440
and days we each cried alone.

402
00:38:30,120 --> 00:38:32,370
Let’s start again, Kin.

403
00:38:32,790 --> 00:38:34,330
No matter how hard it gets,

404
00:38:35,060 --> 00:38:36,420
Than is still right here.

405
00:38:36,750 --> 00:38:39,640
My heart has never belonged
to anyone but Than.

406
00:38:39,780 --> 00:38:43,120
And there’s no space
for anyone else to enter.

407
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:47,830
Today, I’m not marrying
that Grade 10 kid from the court.

408
00:38:48,320 --> 00:38:53,850
I’m marrying a man
who still has the same heart,

409
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:55,890
the heart I loved from day one

410
00:38:56,170 --> 00:38:58,100
and will love until my last day.

411
00:39:01,020 --> 00:39:04,800
Saving the last words for me
is kind of stressful too.

412
00:39:09,970 --> 00:39:13,270
I had my first love
when I was in Grade 10.

413
00:39:13,770 --> 00:39:15,590
And I fell in love with Kin.

414
00:39:16,500 --> 00:39:19,130
From that day until now,

415
00:39:20,020 --> 00:39:21,650
my feelings are the same.

416
00:39:22,520 --> 00:39:27,830
It’s like falling for
the same person every day,

417
00:39:28,420 --> 00:39:31,770
and I never want
to climb out of that fall.

418
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:34,790
I feel incredibly lucky.

419
00:39:36,780 --> 00:39:40,030
That my first love is my only love,

420
00:39:41,130 --> 00:39:43,200
and will become my last.

421
00:39:44,160 --> 00:39:46,210
We’ve had moments
like a romance film,

422
00:39:46,830 --> 00:39:49,060
and moments like a sad one too.

423
00:39:49,990 --> 00:39:53,060
But I’m glad today
it became another movie,

424
00:39:54,300 --> 00:39:57,520
called Reloved.

425
00:40:03,690 --> 00:40:05,850
I love you, Kin.

426
00:40:06,990 --> 00:40:07,870
I love you too, Than.

427
00:40:12,150 --> 00:40:19,250
Kiss! Kiss! Kiss! Kiss!

428
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:29,870
This may be a beautiful ending
to our love story,

429
00:40:31,560 --> 00:40:35,940
but at the same time,
it’s the start of a new chapter,

430
00:40:37,380 --> 00:40:40,070
one we don’t know
will be easy or hard.

431
00:40:41,220 --> 00:40:44,450
The only thing we have is today,

432
00:40:46,900 --> 00:40:49,100
we still choose each other,

433
00:40:49,700 --> 00:40:53,470
love each other,
and promise not to let go easily.

434
00:40:55,170 --> 00:41:00,150
And that alone is enough
to begin our life together.

435
00:41:21,480 --> 00:41:22,330
I want to dance.

436
00:41:22,810 --> 00:41:23,800
-  Me too.
- Let's go.

437
00:41:25,450 --> 00:41:26,010
Where to?

438
00:41:27,690 --> 00:41:29,960
I'll dance with AJ, bro.

439
00:41:30,250 --> 00:41:32,440
- Sorry.
- What?

440
00:41:40,760 --> 00:41:41,300
Please?

441
00:41:42,740 --> 00:41:43,930
No, thanks, Khamin.

442
00:41:44,010 --> 00:41:46,820
Come one, dance with me.

443
00:41:48,620 --> 00:41:49,450
Please.

444
00:41:50,540 --> 00:41:52,430
- Okay, fine.
- Come on.

445
00:41:53,700 --> 00:41:54,440
Let's have fun.

446
00:41:55,940 --> 00:41:58,670
Put on a smiling face. It's wedding.

447
00:41:59,580 --> 00:42:00,160
Okay?

448
00:42:00,740 --> 00:42:03,100
No, give me more. Turn around.

449
00:45:03,520 --> 00:45:05,040
How is it over there?

450
00:45:08,880 --> 00:45:09,850
Are you okay?

451
00:45:15,100 --> 00:45:17,300
There’s something
I’ve never told you.

452
00:45:24,450 --> 00:45:25,500
I love you.

453
00:45:31,060 --> 00:45:32,170
Let’s meet again,

454
00:45:35,160 --> 00:45:35,880
one day.

455
00:45:48,810 --> 00:45:54,280
I wish I could have held you tight

456
00:45:55,110 --> 00:46:00,050
Just one last time before goodbye

457
00:46:00,270 --> 00:46:04,800
Before we’d never meet again

458
00:46:06,030 --> 00:46:12,700
I never regretted
the love we gave away

459
00:46:12,850 --> 00:46:18,920
Never a single regret,
not even one day

460
00:46:19,190 --> 00:46:27,780
Every moment we had
still softly stays

461
00:46:28,640 --> 00:46:33,460
Just missing our last goodbye
we never had to say

462
00:46:36,260 --> 00:46:41,710
I wish I could have held you tight

463
00:46:42,580 --> 00:46:47,590
Just one last time before goodbye

464
00:46:47,750 --> 00:46:52,580
Before we’d never meet again

465
00:46:53,520 --> 00:47:00,320
I never regretted
the love we gave away

466
00:47:00,420 --> 00:47:06,310
Never a single regret,
not even one day

467
00:47:06,710 --> 00:47:15,790
Every moment we had
still softly stays

468
00:47:16,160 --> 00:47:21,600
Just missing our last goodbye
we never had to say

469
00:47:35,990 --> 00:47:38,150
Enough, I don't want to dance anymore.

470
00:47:38,590 --> 00:47:41,180
Change the song. Music.

471
00:47:51,160 --> 00:47:55,200
The day we said goodbye,
the world moved fast,

472
00:47:55,550 --> 00:47:58,520
But my first love stayed,
it always lasts.

473
00:47:59,890 --> 00:48:04,060
Now I see you here,
and I can’t pretend,

474
00:48:04,170 --> 00:48:07,440
My heart still wants you
like it did back then.

475
00:48:09,380 --> 00:48:12,600
It’s just two hearts, so let it be,

476
00:48:12,700 --> 00:48:15,610
We don’t need signs
from the sky or sea.

477
00:48:15,630 --> 00:48:19,820
I almost lost it,
Can you come and heal my heart?

478
00:48:19,850 --> 00:48:24,980
Can we start again,
The same old love, our history?

479
00:48:25,280 --> 00:48:27,380
We both still care,
that’s plain to see,

480
00:48:27,400 --> 00:48:29,700
So why keep living separately?

481
00:48:29,800 --> 00:48:32,650
It’s too hard, I say no more,

482
00:48:33,160 --> 00:48:37,750
Being alone’s too much to bear,
don’t you see?

483
00:48:37,820 --> 00:48:42,430
One glance from your eyes
shows how lonely you must be.

484
00:48:42,700 --> 00:48:45,140
A simple word, a breath so low,

485
00:48:45,410 --> 00:48:50,620
Then, again,
let our love begin to grow.

486
00:50:28,500 --> 00:50:29,230
Morning.

487
00:50:31,150 --> 00:50:32,660
Good morning, Kin.

488
00:50:34,040 --> 00:50:35,810
Our first morning
after the wedding.

489
00:50:36,560 --> 00:50:38,240
Let’s start fresh, Than.

490
00:50:39,950 --> 00:50:41,600
No matter how many times we start,

491
00:50:42,890 --> 00:50:44,560
my love for you never changes, Kin.

492
00:50:49,980 --> 00:50:52,040
Since we’re starting fresh,

493
00:50:53,340 --> 00:50:54,470
want to try something new?

494
00:50:57,450 --> 00:50:58,310
What do you mean?

495
00:51:04,700 --> 00:51:05,390
Kin.

496
00:51:06,860 --> 00:51:07,350
Why?

497
00:51:08,760 --> 00:51:09,360
Isn’t it okay?

498
00:51:33,540 --> 00:51:36,130
We don’t need to start over
with everything, Kin.

499
00:51:37,170 --> 00:51:39,150
Let me handle this one.

500
00:51:40,430 --> 00:51:41,310
I'm good at it.
